## Step 2 — Insert the HISTORICAL schedule row

Once you confirm the filenames look right, run this:

```sql
INSERT INTO own_83650_muse.muse_diffusion_schedules
    (client_reference_id,
     instrument_reference_id,
     diffused_data,
     diffused_filename,
     missing_filename,
     schedule_expression,
     schedule_frequency,
     schedule_time,
     is_active,
     create_user,
     created_at)
SELECT
    ds.client_reference_id,
    ds.instrument_reference_id,
    'HISTORICAL',
    REPLACE(ds.diffused_filename, 'DERIVED', 'H'),
    REPLACE(ds.missing_filename,  'DERIVED', 'H'),
    ds.schedule_expression,
    ds.schedule_frequency,
    ds.schedule_time,
    true,
    'MUSE_INIT',
    CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
FROM own_83650_muse.muse_diffusion_schedules ds
JOIN own_83650_muse.muse_client_reference cr
    ON ds.client_reference_id = cr.id
JOIN own_83650_muse.muse_instrument_reference ir
    ON ds.instrument_reference_id = ir.id
WHERE cr.client_label = 'ESY'
AND ir.instrument_label = 'EQUITY'
AND ds.diffused_data = 'DERIVED'
AND ds.is_active = true
LIMIT 1;
```

